I went to this place solely based on the amount of pretty good reviews.  I have been to my share of Chinese Restaurants around the area so I know the Chinese food in this neighborhood is not good. First off most reviews I read praised the spare ribs. I ordered them and agree the spare ribs are very good. But that is where it ends. Ordered the chicken chow mein another staple of Silver Star. Best I can say is Meh. Fried Rice was plain.  Both of my kids and wife left about 80% of there meal not touched. To top it all off they have a B rating which I don’t like either.  This isn’t even close to a Chop Stix or Danny Szechuan’s in Howard Beach. Good Luck.
